The paper discusses the performance of shared memory parallel codes on multicore systems, which falls under the category of Performance. Therefore, cs.PF is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of hardware counters to characterise the behaviour of each thread, which falls under the category of Architecture. Therefore, cs.AR is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the memory hierarchy and communication networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing. Therefore, cs.DC is the third most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses thread migration strategies, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS is the fourth most likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of OpenMP benchmarks, which falls under the category of Programming Languages. Therefore, cs.PL is the fifth most likely sub-category.
